cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the performance evaluation of content distribution networks and information-centric networks. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper deals with networks of caches and their performance. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the hit ratio and popularity distributions in a network of caches. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses cache replacement policies and their impact on network performance. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the Random replacement policy for networks of caches.
